    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-03T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-03T09:00:00-05:00" n="412"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C/1044: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tittmann</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-03T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 3, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>165. Lester, the Deputy Secretary General, has now assumed complete charge of the
                    administration of the League of Nations as the result of the resignation of the
                    Secretary General which became effective August 31. Avenol therefore has no
                    further connection whatsoever with the League and has merely been given an
                    office in the Library in order that he may wind up his personal affairs. Lester
                    told me this morning that sufficient funds are available to carry on until the
                    end of this year but that thereafter the financial situation is problematical. A
                    budget for 1941 has been prepared and it is now necessary from a legal point of
                    view to find some way to have it approved according to the constitution. Lester
                    still hopes that it will be possible to hold a meeting of the supervisory body
                    in Lisbon for this purpose but if that falls through approval might yet be
                    effected through obtaining the approval of the individual members of the body
                    for submission to the member states. Lester tells me very definitely that it is
                    his intention to keep League of Nations Covenant in being and that insofar as he
                    is concerned liquidation would only take place on the initiative of the member
                    states.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tittmann</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
